The Nigerian Customs Service (NCS) has announced the seizure of $8 million cash at the Muritala Mohammed International Airport Ikeja, Lagos State. Controller General, NCS Hameed Ali, said the consignment packed in a coaster bus was loaded in a six big Bagco bags. The driver of the bus was arrested, while an investigation is ongoing to unravel those behind the deal. Details later.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .